{
  "text": "\u2022 The extension map \u03c0 constructed in Theorem 1.1 above is finite-to-one on sets of full measure, while the extension induced by Hofbauer towers is not. This is perhaps the main advantage of our method, and we expect to use Theorem 1.1 to provide measurable properties such as the almost Borel structure [CITATION_1] .",
